quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,187,"So cause to fall upon us fragments of the sky, if you should be of the truthful."
  26,188,"He said, "
  26,189,"And they denied him, so the punishment of the day of the black cloud seized them. Indeed, it was the punishment of a terrible day."
  33,40,"Muḥammad is not the father of [any] one of your men, but [he is] the Messenger of Allāh and seal [i.e., last] of the prophets. And ever is Allāh, of all things, Knowing."
  33,41,"O you who have believed, remember Allāh with much remembrance"
  33,42,"And exalt Him morning and afternoon."
  34,19,"But [insolently] they said, ",footnotes:1:Stories related to others as lessons or examples.
  34,20,"And Iblees had already confirmed through them{1} his assumption,{2} so they followed him, except for a party of believers.",footnotes:1:i.e., the people of Saba’ or mankind in general.,footnotes:2:That mankind could readily be misled by him.
  34,21,"And he had over them no authority except [it was decreed] that We might make evident who believes in the Hereafter from who is thereof in doubt. And your Lord, over all things, is Guardian.{1}",footnotes:1:Protecting and preserving the existence and attributes of His creations.
  35,4,"And if they deny you, [O Muḥammad] - already were messengers denied before you. And to Allāh are returned [all] matters."
  35,5,"O mankind, indeed the promise of Allāh is truth, so let not the worldly life delude you and be not deceived about Allāh by the Deceiver [i.e., Satan]."
  35,6,"Indeed, Satan is an enemy to you; so take him as an enemy. He only invites his party to be among the companions of the Blaze."